# Richtato Product Conventions

Richtato is an AI-native personal finance app with Monarch Money as the UX north star. Prioritize polished financial dashboards, fast categorization, low-friction editing, and responsive desktop/mobile navigation.

## Agent Defaults

- Read the local code before changing behavior; prefer existing services, components, contexts, and design tokens.
- Keep changes scoped to the requested feature. Do not refactor unrelated modules while fixing docs or behavior.
- Preserve dark/light parity. Use CSS variables and Tailwind tokens such as `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, `primary`, `muted`, and `destructive`.
- Use Tailwind utilities with `cn()` for conditional classes. Avoid inline styles except chart dimensions or library-required values.
- Backend logging uses `loguru.logger`. Frontend code should avoid new `console.log`; use user-facing Sonner toasts or proper error state.
- Icons come from `lucide-react`; notifications use `sonner`; date handling uses `date-fns`.
- For money and dates in UI, use project formatting helpers and user preferences instead of ad hoc `toFixed()` or locale formatting.

## Source Of Truth

- Agent entrypoint: `AGENTS.md`.
- Frontend patterns: `frontend/CLAUDE.md`.
- Backend patterns: `backend/CLAUDE.md`.
- HTTP API: `API_REFERENCE.md` and `/api/docs/` Swagger in a running backend.
- Statement storage path: Google Drive statement storage configured from `/preferences`, backend APIs under `/api/v1/accounts/drive/`, agent uploads through `/api/v1/accounts/agent-statements/`, and stored statement records under `/api/v1/accounts/statements/`. `/upload` is deprecated and removed.
